      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained gnocchi</strong> to the pan with a small splash of <strong>starchy cooking water</strong> and the <strong>chopped basil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min or until the sauce begins to stick to the gnocchi<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato gnocchi</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy cooking water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
